{EAST expects to bid 2NT at his second turn, but WEST gives a positive 2\H 
response and his thinking changes! First he supports \Hs, setting the 
trump suit.

WEST then bids 3\S, showing first round control. EAST tries 4NT (Blackwood) and 
WEST replies 6\C. This shows a \C void and one Ace, obviously the \SA.

EAST bids 6\H, knowing they must lose the \DA.}

