{NORTH might be tempted to blast into Blackwood with his first bid, pushing toward some slam 
in \Hs. He chooses to temporize with a 1\H 
response and is rewarded when SOUTH jumps to 2NT (18-19 points).

The Notrump bid prevents NORTH from using Blackwood, but Gerber 4\C will work just fine. 
When he discovers that SOUTH holds three Aces and one King he can count thirteen tricks.}

